---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { ETSY_SHOP_URL, FACEBOOK_URL } from '../data/etsy';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Coral Reaper"
  description="A small, US-based reef-keeping operation. We grow coral frags and 3D-print the gear we use to keep them — both lines made by hand, both made by us."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Small. Hand-made. Both halves.</h1>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Coral Reaper is a small, US-based reef-keeping operation built
          around two things we make ourselves: aquacultured coral frags
          and 3D-printed reef accessories.
        </p>

        <h2>What we sell today</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Coral frags</strong> — aquacultured pieces grown in our
            own system, photographed in our own racks. <strong>Local pickup
            only</strong> right now. We're not set up to ship live coral
            overnight yet, but we will be. <a href="/frags">See current inventory →</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>3D-printed reef gear</strong> — frag racks, photo boxes,
            light shades, tray accessories. Designed for our own setup first;
            listed on Etsy when they're ready for other reefers.
            <a href={ETSY_SHOP_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Shop on Etsy ↗</a>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why we make our own gear</h2>
        <p>
          We started with corals. The 3D printer was for accessories nobody
          else made — frag racks sized for our system, photo boxes that fit
          them, light shades that block spill. When tank friends asked where
          we got them, we listed a few. Now the gear funds the corals.
        </p>
        <p>
          The two product lines stay connected on purpose. Every frag photo
          on this site was shot in a rack we designed. The gear isn't a
          side hustle — it's part of the same workshop.
        </p>

        <h2>How we ship</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Frags</strong> — local pickup only. Coordinate via the
            <a href="/contact">contact form</a> or
            <a href={FACEBOOK_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Facebook</a>.
            Overnight shipping for live coral is on the roadmap, not the menu yet.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Gear</strong> — ships nationwide through our Etsy shop.
            Standard processing, tracking, the usual. 5★ from every buyer
            so far.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What's next</h2>
        <p>
          See the <a href="/drops">roadmap</a>. Short version: more frag
          inventory, more gear designs, eventually shipped frags overnight,
          eventually live drops. We're building deliberately, one piece at a time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .narrow { max-width: 760px; }

  .prose {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-bone);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose p {
    color: var(--color-bone-dim);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .prose ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .prose ul li {
    color: var(--color-bone-dim);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .prose strong { color: var(--color-bone); }
</style>
